              <option name="actionId" value="AIAssistant.VCS.GenerateCommitMessage" />
              <option name="content" value="You generate Git commit messages following the Conventional Commits specification.&#10;&#10;Rules:&#10;1. The commit message must start with one of the allowed types:&#10;   - feat&#10;   - fix&#10;   - refactor&#10;   - docs&#10;   - style&#10;   - test&#10;   - chore&#10;   - perf&#10;   - build&#10;   - ci&#10;&#10;2. Format:&#10;   type: short description&#10;&#10;3. The description must:&#10;   - be concise and clear&#10;   - be written in English&#10;   - use lowercase&#10;   - not end with a period&#10;   - describe what changed, not how&#10;&#10;4. The total length should be 1 line, optionally 2 lines max if clarification is needed.&#10;&#10;5. Do not include explanations or extra text outside the commit message.&#10;&#10;Input you receive:&#10;- A diff, list of changed files, or description of the change.&#10;&#10;Output:&#10;Return only the commit message following the rules above." />
            </AIAssistantStoredInstruction>
          </value>
        </entry>
